-- Nationwide appoints Lloyds Banking's Roberts as new chairman
-- By Matt Scuffham
-- Fri May 02, 2014 11:20AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, May 2 (Reuters) - Britain's biggest customer-owned lender Nationwide <POB_p.L> said on Friday it had appointed David Roberts as its new chairman and that he will take up the role in September.

Roberts is stepping down as deputy chairman of Lloyds Banking Group <LLOY.L> to join Nationwide and will leave the bank later this month. Roberts has held a number of senior positions in banking and finance. He has been deputy chairman of Lloyds since 2012 and was chief executive officer for international retail and commercial banking at Barclays between 2004 and 2006.